sentences: In 1989 she won the Metropolitan Opera National Council Auditions.
She went to school at 'Instituto Anglo Chileno' (now 'Colegio Anglo Maipu')
She currently teaches voice students in Santiago.
In 2009 she sang at the "Festival de Viña del Mar" where she won all the prizes of the festival (silver torch, golden torch and silver seagull)
In 2009 she sang at the "Festival de Viña del Mar" where she won all the prizes of the festival (silver torch, golden torch and silver seagull)
She debuted at the Metropolitan Opera in the role of Mimì in La Bohème in 1991 and sang that role twenty times.

She sang there the role of Violetta in La Traviata in 1993 (19 times), the roles of Liù in Turandot and Micaela in Carmen in 1996, Marguerite in Faust in 1997, Lina in Stiffelio in 1998, Nedda in I Pagliacci and Margherita/Elena in Mefistofele in 1999, Cio-Cio-San in Madama Butterfly in 2001, Elizabeth of Valois in Don Carlo in 2002 and Luisa in Luisa Miller in 2006.
